&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and reliable individual to join Gastroenterology as an IBD Administrator working for the IBD team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be required to maintain the IBD Register, organise and minute IBD weekly MDTs as well as secretarial and personal assistant support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will require excellent communication and organisational skills and be able to manage your workload. You will need to be self-motivated, able to work in a calm, logical, and methodical way but be able to multi-task whilst dealing with frequent interruptions. You will be used to working to tight deadlines and be used to dealing with people at all levels both inside and outside of the organisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This a part time role, working 18 hours per week between the core hours of 8.30am and 5pm.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Proposed Interview Date: Week beginning Monday 16th November 2020.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Caitlin Hill - Clinical Admin Lead on&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; 07788361841.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rebekah Watts - Team Leader. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;rebekah.watts1@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; or call 01872 253027.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
